{"date":"Thu, 15 Jul 2021 00:00:00 GMT","img_url":"https://english.khabarhub.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Nepal-Rastra-Bank1.jpg","keywords":["from","atm","withdrawing","interbank","to","the","bfis","transactions","a","for","jan","khabarhub","nrb","charge"],"summary":"NRB allows BFIs to charge for inter-bank ATM transactions from Jan 14KATHMANDU: You will be charged for withdrawing money from ATMs other than belonging to your bank from January 14.\nThe Nepal Rastra Bank (NRB) on Thursday issued a directive allowing banks and financial institutions from charging fees for inter-bank ATM transactions.\nBanks and financial institutions were not allowed to charge a fee for withdrawing money from another bank\u2019s ATM since March when the government had enforced a lockdown to stem the spread of the coronavirus.\nCustomers will still be able to conduct two monthly inter-bank ATM withdrawals for free.\nNRB has made an arrangement to charge up to Rs 20 per transaction for more than two transactions.","text":"NRB allows BFIs to charge for inter-bank ATM transactions from Jan 14\n\nKATHMANDU: You will be charged for withdrawing money from ATMs other than belonging to your bank from January 14.\n\nThe Nepal Rastra Bank (NRB) on Thursday issued a directive allowing banks and financial institutions from charging fees for inter-bank ATM transactions.\n\nBanks and financial institutions were not allowed to charge a fee for withdrawing money from another bank\u2019s ATM since March when the government had enforced a lockdown to stem the spread of the coronavirus.\n\nCustomers will still be able to conduct two monthly inter-bank ATM withdrawals for free. NRB has made an arrangement to charge up to Rs 20 per transaction for more than two transactions.","title":"NRB allows BFIs to charge for inter-bank ATM transactions from Jan 14 - Khabarhub","url":"http://english.khabarhub.com/2021/07/154783/","video":[]}
